# Client-Side Release Validation Suite Plan

Expose the PRISM Strict Release Validation tests to the operator/agent console. This enables the operator to run strict gate validation directly from the web interface, monitor the real-time execution console, and view the status of each validation gate with premium UI visuals.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> We will add a new **PRISM Release Validation Suite** panel directly to the **Computer Control** tab (`tab-computer.html`). This keeps local system execution actions grouped together under a unified interface.

## Proposed Changes

We will introduce a background execution system for release validation, expose the required backend routes, and build a beautiful, reactive frontend panel.

---

### Backend Components

#### [MODIFY] [dashboard-service.ts](file:///d:/Projects/Prism/src/core/operator/dashboard-service.ts)
- Implement `activeValidationPid` to track background execution.
- Implement `/api/release-validation/run` (`POST`):
  - Check if validation is already running (returns 409).
  - Clear any previous run log (`artifacts/benchmarks/release-validation.log`).
  - Spawn `node dist/src/benchmarks/release-validation.js --strict` detached.
  - Pipe/redirect stdout and stderr to the log file.
  - Return `202 Accepted` with PID.
- Implement `/api/release-validation/status` (`GET`):
  - Check if the process is running using `process.kill(activePid, 0)`.
  - Read `artifacts/benchmarks/release-validation.log` (if it exists) to supply console logs.
  - Read `artifacts/benchmarks/release-validation.json` (if it exists) to supply structural gate status data.
  - Return a consolidated JSON payload containing `running`, `pid`, `log`, `gates`, `passed`, and `generatedAt`.

